The Mac OS X failure is rather interesting
 - since #28760 linting is done on all OSes;
 - so Mac OS X lints freebsd and linux as well;
 - git clone checks out sources to `/Users/MacM1-1-worker/ci/task-6679635427065856`;
 - golangci-lint fails to read _some_ files from `/Users/MacM1-1-worker/ci/task-4586354266341376`;

 So it looks like
  - golangci-lint cache is not working when the sources are checked out into a temp directory;
  - maybe it's best to perform linting on one platform only (and ditch the native linting for mac os x and freebsd).

This is what https://github.com/podman-io/podman-sandbox/pull/9 does (among the other things). The checkout path is also fixed in there.

As a stop-gap measure, I propose https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/28797.
